# Engineering Standards

## Defaults
- Private repos by default
- Fork → clone workflow
- First commit: PROJECT_SPEC.md + standards files

## Architecture
- Cheap: minimize costs, use free tiers
- Scalable: cloud-first, horizontal scaling
- Low LOC: minimal code, maximum impact
- Minimal deps: fewer dependencies = fewer vulnerabilities

## Python
- 3.11+ for apps, 3.9+ for libraries
- Type hints on public APIs
- Pydantic for data validation at boundaries

## Quality
- 80%+ test coverage on core logic
- CI on every PR: lint + typecheck + test
- Schemas at data boundaries

## Safety
- DRY RUN for cleanup operations
- No auto-delete; explicit confirmation required
- Prefer archive over delete
- Log intent before executing

## Model Selection
- Opus: architecture, code review, novel problems
- Sonnet: standard dev, features, docs (default)
- Cheap: bulk, repetitive, formatting
- Budget rule: reserve 10% for critical Opus decisions

## Priority
1. CI/CD setup
2. Test infrastructure
3. Core functionality
4. Features
5. Documentation
